      "content": "It is incredibly exhausting to feel like your entire existence has been a performance that suddenly ended, leaving you wondering if you truly mattered at all. That feeling of emptiness, where the very concept of \"humanity\" feels hollow without the external validation you relied on, is a painful realization that many face. While it may seem like there is nothing left, this profound shift often marks the beginning of a necessary, quieter period to rebuild a sense of self that isn't tied to who you thought you should be.",
      "source": "target",
